<SECOND>AM-Ship Mayday,0163</SECOND>
<HEAD>Coast Guard Seeking Sinking Sport Fishing Boat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PORTSMOUTH, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 52-foot sport fishing boat with 10
people aboard apparently sank Thursday night off the Virginia coast,
the Coast Guard said.
   The Blue Goose, described as a Hatteras-type fishing vessel,
radioed at 9:30 p.m. that it was taking on water, said Coast Guard
spokesman Kenneth Crump.
   The Coast Guard sent a helicopter and two patrol boats to aid the
vessel, which reported its position as about five miles off Virginia
Beach. ``We're assuming it did go down. We haven't had any contact
with the vessel since 10:30 p.m.,'' Crump said.
   The helicopter from Elizabeth City, N.C., arrived on the scene
just before 11 p.m., and began its search. The patrol boats were en
route from the Little Creek Coast Guard Station, and a Navy vessel
was steaming to the scene, he said.
   Crump said the helicopter had not spotted any of the vessel's
occupants.
