<HEAD>North Says South Korean Warships Violated Territorial Waters</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS two grafs to CORRECT to warships sted battleships. Picks
up graf 3 pvs, `The two ...'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two South Korean warships violated North Korea's
territorial waters Thursday, the North's official news agency said.
   The warships crossed into North Korea's territorial waters off
Tungsangot in the Yellow Sea between China and the Korean peninsula
before dawn said the Central News Agency.
   The two ships ``fled south in haste'' when North Korean patrol
boats tried to approach them, according to the agency, monitored in
Tokyo.
