on the divided peninsula. U.S. and South Korean officials say they
are defensive and vital to South Korea's security.
   About 43,000 U.S. troops stationed in South Korea under a mutual
defense pact are taking part in the maneuvers, along with 30,000
American troops stationed in the United States and other Asian
nations.
   The Korean peninsula was divided in 1945 at the end of World War
II. The countries fought a bloody three-year war after North Korea
invaded the South in 1950.
