<FIRST>r a PM-Gunman-Chronology     03-24 0270</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Gunman-Chronology,0278</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Gunman's Rampage, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LITTLETON, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a chronology of Thursday's
rampage that left two women dead, a third raped, a hostage wounded,
two deputies wounded and the gunman dead of a self-inflicted gunshot
wound to the head.
   _5 a.m. Officers respond to a emergency phone call in Littleton,
find the home's garage door open and the resident, Beverly J.
Swartz, 47, and her car missing.
   _6:38 a.m. Officers respond to reports of a shooting and find the
bodies of Swartz and her mother-in-law, Janice Irene Swartz, 68,
bound and shot in the elder woman's home in Douglas County. Janice
Swartz' husband, Oscar, was found in the house and suffering from
shock. He was able to get free and call for help. Beverly Swartz's
husband, Ralph, was summoned to the scene and also was suffering
from shock.
   _6:38-8 a.m. The gunman then stole a car and drove 10 miles to
another Douglas County subdivision, where he broke into a house,
held a man, woman and child at gunpoint and then raped the woman.
   _8:30 a.m. The gunman drove into a fence and fled on foot,
setting of a massive, door-to-door manhunt.
   _2:43 p.m. Arapahoe County Sheriff's deputies Arthur L. Hilton,
37, and Daniel N. Thomas, 36, are shot and wounded as they entered a
townhouse in the Arapahoe Ridge subdivision.
   _2:44 p.m. The gunman then shot Jake Carper, 18, a hostage he had
held in the townhouse, went upstairs and shot himself in the head.
   _5:56 p.m. Swedish Medical Center reports that suspect Eugene
Thompson Jr., 20, of Littleton, died of the gunshot wound.
</TEXT>
