<SECOND>PM-South Africa-Accident,0139</SECOND>
<HEAD>22 Black Workers Killed When Truck Overturns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A lumber truck carrying black
workers home for the holiday weekend overturned on a mountain road,
killing 22 men and injuring 24, police said today.
   Capt. Gert Nel, a police spokesman in the Natal Province town of
Vryheid, said the driver was among those killed when the truck
flipped over while rounding a curve on a gravel road Thursday
afternoon.
   The men were employees of the H. L. and H. Forest Products
company in Vryheid, about 120 miles north of the port of Durban, and
were being driven to their villages in the nearby black homeland of
KwaZulu.
   Nel said 21 of the men died immediately and one died in a
hospital today. Authorities said tour were reported in serious
condition today.
