<HEAD>Three Cases of Condoms Stolen from Warehouse</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANDERSON, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Investigators are looking into the theft of
three cases of condoms that an official said apparently were stolen
for ``recreational purposes.''
   Reported missing Wednesday were 1,728 individually wrapped latex
condoms that had been in a warehouse at Schmid Laboratories. The
condoms had a maximum retail value of $700 to $800.
   ``The fact that they didn't take but a few makes us believe they
took them for recreational purposes,'' said Roy Kelly, personnel
manager for Schmid, which also makes toothpaste, contraceptive foams
and jellies.
   Company officials say they probably will not find out who took
the condoms, which were awaiting shipment to a distribution center,
but hope whoever stole them will act responsibly.
   ``If nothing else, maybe it'll make a customer for us,'' Kelly
said.
