<HEAD>Jetliner Gets Stuck in Pothole</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The front wheel of a jetliner with
83 people aboard got stuck in a runway pothole at an airport in
northwestern Brazil, but no one was injured, an official said Friday.
   The Varig airlines Boeing 737 had just landed Thursday at
Uberlandia, 600 miles northwest of Rio, after a flight from the
northern city of Belem, a spokeswoman for the Brazilian airline said.
   As it was taxiing to the gate, the front wheel slipped into a
runway pothole and jammed. The passengers were taken from the plane,
which was later towed from the runway, and the pothole was being
repaired, the spokeswoman said.
