<UNK>Political Activist Given 15-Month Suspended Sentence</UNK>
<DATELINE>PRAGUE, Czecholsovakia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dusan Skala, an independent
publisher and political activist, was given a suspended sentence of
15 months after a one-day trial Friday, a leading dissident
reported.
   Anna Sabatova of the Charter 77 human rights organization said
the trial was held in a town near Brno, 125 miles east of Prague,
and Skala was convicted of incitement in connection with a banned
rally last October.
   Communist authorities began a crackdown on dissidents following
anti-government protests in August, October and January.
   Earlier this week an appeals court in Prague gave playwright
Vaclav Havel an eight-month sentence.
   Seven other activists were jailed, fined or given suspended
sentences last month.
