<HEAD>Reports Radioactive Oregano Seized In Sicily</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CATANIA, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Packages of radioactive oregano were
seized by police in the Sicilian cities of Catania and Syracuse,
the Italian news agency ANSA reported Friday.
   It said the oregano, imported by the Ducros Freres firm, was
confiscated after tests by the health institute in Catania
determined it had radiation levels higher than limits set by the
European Economic Community.
   ANSA said the Italian Ministry of Health is analyzing samples of
imported thyme and dried mushrooms for radiation levels.
   The Agency, in its report late Friday, did not say in what
country or countries the spices and mushrooms were grown or give a
possible reason for the radiation. Health officials could not be
reached immediately for comment.
   ANSA also said the Health Ministry in Rome ordered the Catania
tests but did not say what prompted the order.
