<HEAD>LaserPhoto LON3</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   STOKE-UPON-TRENT, England (AP) _ A fairground cable car buffeted
by strong winds became entangled in communications lines Friday,
trapping 11 people for more than two hours nearly 100 feet above
ground, an official said.
   The Skyride at Alton Towers leisure park in western England came
to a halt when one of three cable cars carrying 27 people became
entangled with overhead wires after a sharp gust of wind, a park
