<SECOND>AM-Abortion-Arrest,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Accused of Aborting Full-Term Baby Booked for Murder</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN BERNARDINO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman accused of performing an
abortion on herself to get rid of her full-term fetus was arrested
for investigation of murder, police said Thursday.
   Margarita Gutierrez, 19, was booked at the San Bernardino Medical
Center jail ward, where she was listed in good condition Thursday
following her arrest at her home Wednesday, said Sgt. Dan Hernandez.
   ``She apparently intentionally aborted her child, resulting in
the death of the child,'' he said.
   The boy, whom police called ``baby Gutierrez,'' was taken to the
San Bernardino County Coroner's Office, where an autopsy was
scheduled for Friday.
   ``It will determine whether it was a stillborn delivery or an
aborted fetus,'' said Deputy Coroner Tom Dewhurst.
   The autopsy will also determine how old the fetus was. Sgt. Bob
Evans said police believe it was full-term.
   Ms. Gutierrez was arrested by San Bernardino police after they
were contacted by a doctor who alerted them to the woman. Evans said
authorities haven't yet determined a motive or how the delivery
occurred.
