<FIRST>r f AM-WoolOutput     03-24 0094</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Wool Output,0098</SECOND>
<HEAD>Up 5 Percent in 1989</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. wool production increased 5 percent last
year to 89.2 million pounds, the Agriculture Department said Friday.
   The number of sheep shorn totaled 11.5 million head, also up 5
percent, the department's Agricultural Statistics Board said in its
annual report. The average fleece weight was 7.78 pounds, up
fractionally from 1987.
   Total value of wool shorn was estimated at $125 million, a 62
percent increase from $77.1 million in 1987. Prices averaged $1.38
per pound, compared with 91.7 cents a year earlier.
</TEXT>
